1 becomes false, the state agency shall disqualify the contractor or potential contractor from
2 contracting with the state agency for a period of three years from the time of the determi-
3 nation.
4 (5) As used in this section:
5 (a) “Contractor” means a person to whom a state agency has awarded a contract.
6 (b) “Prospective contractor” means any person who submits a bid or proposal for a con-
7 tract with a state agency.
8 (c) “State agency” means every state officer, board, commission, department, institution,
9 branch or agency of the state government whose costs are paid wholly or in part from funds
10 held in the State Treasury.
11 (d) “Transportation subcontract” means a subcontract for services involving the trans-
12 portation of humans.
13 SECTION 2. (1) A state agency that awards a grant to a recipient shall require the re-
14 cipient to execute an agreement as described in subsection (2) of this section as a condition
15 of receiving grant moneys.
16 (2) An agreement under this section must:
17 (a) Require the recipient to attest, before receiving grant moneys, that the recipient is
18 not and will not be under an agreement with any federal agency to provide transportation
19 services for individuals detained by the federal agency for the purpose of deportation from
20 the United States, except in accordance with an order of a federal court, not including ad-
21 ministrative courts; and
22 (b) Require the recipient to repay the grant moneys to the state agency if the state
23 agency determines that the attestation is false or subsequently becomes false.
24 (3) As used in this section:
25 (a) “Grant” means an award of moneys by a state agency to a person or entity other than
26 a public body, as defined in ORS 174.109, that is made under terms that do not require the
27 repayment of the moneys unless the recipient breaches specified obligations.
28 (b) “State agency” has the meaning given that term in section 1 of this 2026 Act.
29 SECTION 3. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
30 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
31 on its passage.
